# Mandatory `data-testid` convention

## Goal

- Playwright E2E selectors must be **`getByTestId()` first**.
- The app must provide **robust, stable, unique** `data-testid` attributes to support that.

## Requirements (mandatory)

- **All interactive elements must have `data-testid`** in `app/**` and `components/**`.
  - Includes `button`, `input`, `textarea`, `select`, `a`, and any element with click/keyboard handlers.
- **All screen roots and test-critical semantic containers must have `data-testid`**.
  - Includes screen `<main>` roots, cards/panels/lists/rows used by E2E flows, and key state containers (locked/empty/error/success).
- Non-interactive presentational wrappers (`div`/`span` used only for layout/text) do not require mandatory IDs unless tests rely on them.
- **No ad-hoc strings**: build IDs using the shared helper in `lib/testIds.ts`.
- **No localized/copy text** in test ids:
  - Do not derive IDs from Hebrew strings, workbook prompts, visible labels, or any user input.
  - Use stable internal identifiers instead (`grade`, `day.id`, `strand.id`, `exercise.id`, etc.).
- **Custom components must forward** `data-testid` to a real DOM root element.
  - If a component renders an intrinsic element, it must accept `data-testid` (or `testId`) and pass it through.

## ID structure (contract)

- Prefix all IDs with `km.` (see `lib/testIds.ts`).
- Prefer stable “Tier‑1” anchors for screens/cards/exercises, then derive children from those anchors.

## Component composition (mandatory)

- **Tier‑1 anchors live on the screen root** (`<main>`): use `testIds.screen.*.root(...)` there.
- **Nested blocks must use `childTid()`** from the Tier‑1 anchor (e.g. `childTid(testIds.screen.day.root(...), "panel")`).
- **Never reuse the same `data-testid` on multiple elements** (Playwright strict mode treats that as ambiguous).
  - If you need both a screen root and an inner panel id, **keep the root** on `<main>` and use `childTid(root, ...)` for the panel.

## Testing guidance

- Prefer `page.getByTestId(testIds....)` to locate elements.
- Avoid brittle selectors:
  - XPath (`locator('xpath=...')`)
  - selectors derived from content strings (e.g. `exercise.prompt`)
  - unscoped tag-name selectors (`page.locator('button').first()`)

## Legacy migration policy (`km.autogen.*`)

- Existing legacy `km.autogen.*` IDs are allowed temporarily.
- New code and edited code must use helper-based IDs from `lib/testIds.ts` + `childTid()`.
- When touching a component that still uses `km.autogen.*`, migrate at least the edited subtree to helper-based IDs.
- Before merge, run `npm run check:testids` and fix reported violations.

